---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Who Ben Atkins is — IT by day, curious about everything else."
  orbColor="rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.15)"
>
  <header class="mb-12">
    <h1
      class="text-4xl font-bold mb-3"
      style="font-family: var(--font-display); color: var(--color-heading);"
    >
      About
    </h1>
    <p style="color: var(--color-muted);">The longer version.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="flex flex-col gap-10" style="color: var(--color-body);">

    <section>
      <h2
        class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
        style="color: var(--color-muted);"
      >
        Career
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Six years of IT support and systems administration experience spanning healthcare (VUMC)
        and financial services (LBMC), with consistent delivery across varying compliance frameworks
        and operational demands.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">
        Core competencies include identity and access management, M365/Azure administration,
        endpoint lifecycle management, hardware deployment, PowerShell automation, and SOC 2
        compliance coordination. Supplemental front-end development skills enable me to build
        solutions proactively, not just resolve issues reactively.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2
        class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
        style="color: var(--color-muted);"
      >
        Background
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Nashville native. B.A. in Psychology with a minor in Business Administration from the
        University of Tennessee. Started my career in healthcare, where working directly with
        patients and staff built a strong foundation in communication and customer service.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
        While working in healthcare, I found myself increasingly drawn to the technical side of
        how systems worked and how they could be improved. Pondering a career change, I took
        courses in Python and web development at Red Rocks Community College.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Once I officially decided to pursue a career in tech, I moved back to Nashville and
        committed fully, completing Nashville Software School's full-stack web development bootcamp
        in 2017 with extensive training in JavaScript, React, and modern development practices.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">
        Upon entering the IT field shortly after, each role has been a continuous education: new
        tools, new challenges, new ways to grow.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2
        class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
        style="color: var(--color-muted);"
      >
        Passions
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Dedicated gamer. It's more than just a hobby. Genuinely passionate about game design,
        mechanical innovation, and clean, intuitive UX/UI. Core genres include Souls-likes,
        Metroidvanias, and JRPGs, with Rocket League as a perpetual fixture in the background.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Passionate about indie music, spanning rock, pop, and hip-hop. Always digging for the
        next hidden gem.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">
        Fiercely competitive fantasy football manager with a borderline unhealthy level of
        investment and an imperviousness to inevitable, annual heartbreak.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="pt-2 border-t border-[#2a2a2a]">
      <div class="flex gap-5 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/Batkins44"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="hover:text-[#60a5fa] transition-colors duration-200"
        >
          GitHub
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/batkins44"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="hover:text-[#60a5fa] transition-colors duration-200"
        >
          LinkedIn
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
